        <p> ___Twig_token_1___ I drove son to Ahrensburg. Note: Small car on the highway near Sturm are not fun! </p>
        <p> When I arrived in Ahrensburg, I collected Basti and luggage and we drove straight to the airport. There we got rid of the rental car really quickly and easily. Now we still had plenty of time to boarding. So first unpacked and breakfast in the "Restaurant Zur Goldenen M&ouml;we". We wanted to give up the luggage two hours before departure. </p>
        <p> Panic: Something is wrong with my entry confirmation for Canada. When applying for the ETA, I did not enter the pass number correctly. One O was actually a 0. As we were allowed to learn now, there are no O&rsquo;s in pass numbers. Fortunately, the lady at the counter could clarify the problem. Thanks to our excellent preparation, we also passed the security check. </p>
        <p> The flight to London Heathrow was uneventful except for the fact that British Airways is now taking money for drinks on short -haul flights. When we arrived in London early, we had to pass a security check again. So unpack all electronic devices. And we have some of them. </p>

