        <p> The next shock on the boarding check (which we had on the cell phone). "Please register at the counter". There we were informed that we were upgraded to the World Traveler Plus class. Super!!! So with grin on the face a bit in the Harry Potter Shop and then eaten a few fries. In the waiting area, we tried to get into our thrombosis socks under laughter cramps. Which almost worked. </p>
        <p> Getting into the Boing 787 to Montreal started with half an hour late. We were allowed to go to the plane again. Our places were great. We were able to sit together and even make our legs long. There were pillows, blankets, noise -insulating headphones and delicious food. And the drinks were also included. So first we order beer and whiskey to start our trip. The plane then started with a delay of 1.5 hours at 18:12 because the pushback vehicle was broken. With a little tailwind we landed 19:52 in Montreal. Local time, of course. Now we have a time shift of 6 hours to Germany. </p>
        <p> The entry to Canada was surprisingly smooth. Scan passport, take a photo, written and oral test and we were already in Canada. </p>
        <p> Now the most important thing: organize phone cards for your cell phone. That was also quick and so the Uber delivered us around 9:30 p.m. in the Hotel Bestwestern. The room was ok, we wandered a little more and then went to bed on time. </p>
        <p> Good night out there. </p>
